Package: libzrtpcpp4
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: GNU ZRTP library for secure voice communication
 This library provides ZRTP (Zimmermann Real-time Transport Protocol) support
 for secure voice communication. It implements the ZRTP key agreement protocol
 as specified in RFC 6189, allowing ad-hoc key negotiation for Secure RTP
 (SRTP) sessions.
 .
 Features include:
  * Multi-stream mode support
  * Multiple Diffie-Hellman key exchange methods (2048, 3072, 4096 bit)
  * Elliptic curve cryptography (NIST curves, Curve25519, Curve448)
  * Multiple cipher suites (AES-128/256, Twofish-128/256)
  * Skein hash and MAC algorithms
  * Short Authentication String (SAS) verification
 .
 This package contains the shared library needed to run applications
 that use libzrtpcpp.

Package: libzrtpcpp-dev
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libzrtpcpp4 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: libzrtpcpp-doc
Description: Development files for GNU ZRTP library
 This package contains the header files, static libraries, and development
 documentation needed to build applications that use the GNU ZRTP library.
 .
 ZRTP (Zimmermann Real-time Transport Protocol) is a key agreement protocol
 that allows two parties to establish a secure SRTP session without requiring
 a pre-shared secret or PKI infrastructure.
 .
 Install this package if you want to develop applications that integrate
 ZRTP-based encryption.